{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:37:40.663Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"g1kzakqk","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Platform: Phase 3 Interactive Tools & Phase 4 FastAPI Backend Contracts\n  2 | \n  3 | This document establishes the strategic architectural interface between the high-fidelity client-side interactive tools built in **Phase 3** and the future enterprise-grade, high-performance **FastAPI backend (Phase 4)**. \n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## 1. Executive Architecture Overview\n  8 | \n  9 | In Phase 3, GFF AI delivers an **unmatched, premium, frontend-only interactive suite** spanning the *Build Hub* workspace. These tools (Blueprint Builder, Readiness Assessment, ROI Calculator, RFP/Proposal Builder, Client Sandbox, Foundry Studio workflow canvas, and Agent Marketplace) run fully on client-side state machine architectures to maximize fluid responsiveness, respect data privacy boundaries, and ensure flawless offline capability during presentation.\n 10 | \n 11 | In Phase 4, these interactive tools will transition from local state management to a robust, containerized Python **FastAPI backend**. This migration will enable secure multi-user collaboration, real-time agent execution orchestration, persistent database storage, and integrations with enterprise identity providers.\n 12 | \n 13 | ### 1.1. Hybrid Architecture Topology\n 14 | \n 15 | ```\n 16 | +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 17 | |                               CLIENT BROWSER (Next.js)                          |\n 18 | |                                                                                 |\n 19 | |  +-------------------------+   +------------------------+   +----------------+  |\n 20 | |  |  Build Hub Workspace    |   |  Interactive Tools UI  |   | Local Storage  |  |\n 21 | |  |  (React/Next.js/Framer) |   |  (React Hook Form/Zod) |   | & Session Cache|  |\n 22 | |  +------------+------------+   +-----------+------------+   +--------+-------+  |\n 23 | |               |                            |                         |          |\n 24 | +---------------|----------------------------|-------------------------|----------+\n 25 |                 | SECURE TLS (HTTPS)         |                         | Sync\n 26 |                 |                            |                         | (Future Phase 4)\n 27 |                 v                            v                         v\n 28 | +--------------------------------------------+------------------------------------+\n 29 | |                             FUTURE FASTAPI BACKEND SERVICES                     |\n 30 | |                                                                                 |\n 31 | |   +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+  |\n 32 | |   |                       API Router & Gateway Controller                    |  |\n 33 | |   |         - Pydantic Input Validation      - JWT/OTP Security Middleware   |  |\n 34 | |   |         - SlowAPI Rate Limiter           - CORS Policy Manager           |  |\n 35 | |   +----+--------------------+--------------------+--------------------+----+  |\n 36 | |        |                    |                    |                    |         |\n 37 | |        v                    v                    v                    v         |\n 38 | |  +-----------+        +-----------+        +-----------+        +------------+  |\n 39 | |  | Cache     |        | Database  |        | Object    |        | Email /    |  |\n 40 | |  | (Redis)   |        | (Postgres)|        | Store     |        | OTP Engine |  |\n 41 | |  | - OTPs    |        | - Users   |        | (AWS S3)  |        | (SES /     |  |\n 42 | |  | - Session |        | - Proposls|        | - PDFs    |        | SendGrid)  |  |\n 43 | |  | - RateLim |        | - Flows   |        | - Configs |        | - Auth     |  |\n 44 | |  +-----------+        +-----------+        +-----------+        +------------+  |\n 45 | +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 46 | ```\n 47 | \n 48 | ---\n 49 | \n 50 | ## 2. Phase 3 Interactive Tools Status\n 51 | \n 52 | The table below catalogs what has been fully implemented inside the Next.js workspace for Phase 3, specifying where the boundary of \"frontend-only simulation\" lies and what operations will be handled by the FastAPI microservices in Phase 4.\n 53 | \n 54 | | Interactive Tool | Phase 3 Frontend Capability | Future Phase 4 Backend Integration |\n 55 | | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n 56 | | **Blueprint Builder** | Interactive multi-step journey, dynamic architecture node rendering, PDF download simulation, client-side share link creation. | Persistent storage, real-time database generation, AI-generated custom system components, PDF generation in Python. |\n 57 | | **Readiness Assessment** | Comprehensive 5-category evaluation matrix, scoring weights, remediation checklists, local results storage. | Enterprise aggregation, comparative industry benchmarking, administrative audit trails. |\n 58 | | **ROI Calculator** | Real-time strategic financial formula processor (TCO, NPV, Payback, FTE reallocation) with visual charts. | High-fidelity model adjustment, customizable exportable spreadsheets, corporate database storage. |\n 59 | | **Proposal Builder**| Custom RFP requirements intake, step-by-step modular timeline constructor, proposal compiler. | Large Language Model (LLM) customized RFP generation, direct client PDF render pipeline, collaborative drafting. |\n 60 | | **Client Sandbox** | Interactive shell with terminal output simulation, sample developer tasks, live log visualizer. | Dockerized ephemeral execution environments, actual command execution, sandboxed Python interpreters. |\n 61 | | **Foundry Studio** | Drag-and-drop multi-agent workflow DAG designer, canvas node interaction, cyclical validation checks. | DAG execution engine, Celery task broker synchronization, deployment manifest compiles. |\n 62 | | **Agent Marketplace** | Filterable catalog of pre-configured enterprise agent definitions, installation toggles. | Real-time agent downloads, version control, third-party author portal uploads, licensing, secure keys. |\n 63 | \n 64 | ---\n 65 | \n 66 | ## 3. Phase 4 Target Backend System Architecture\n 67 | \n 68 | To ensure premium execution, the FastAPI backend will utilize a robust architectural stack:\n 69 | \n 70 | 1. **FastAPI Framework (Python 3.12+)**: Leveraging high-performance `asyncio` for scalable multi-connection handling. FastAPI natively exports strict OpenAPI schemas via Redoc or Swagger.\n 71 | 2. **Relational Database (PostgreSQL 16+)**: Managed relational store utilizing SQLAlchemy ORM or SQLModel. Houses user credentials, enterprise workflows, generated proposals, audit histories, and compliance records.\n 72 | 3. **In-Memory Cache (Redis 7+)**: Used for high-speed rate-limiting, short-term OTP validation tokens, and secure JWT blacklist/session states.\n 73 | 4. **AWS S3 or S3-Compatible Object Storage**: Enterprise repository for archiving dynamically compiled PDF blueprints, corporate agreements, custom proposals, and downloadable sandbox snapshots. \n 74 | 5. **No AWS or Cloud Credentials in Phase 3**: In compliance with security policies, all cloud, database, and SMTP services remain abstractly represented via strict, un-hydrated configuration variables.\n 75 | 6. **Authentication Flow**: Completely passwordless, secure, enterprise-tailored One-Time Password (OTP) validation delivered to business emails. Supports corporate domains only, utilizing an abstract communication dispatcher layer (SES, Mailgun, or SendGrid).\n 76 | \n 77 | ---\n 78 | \n 79 | ## 4. FastAPI API Endpoint Catalog\n 80 | \n 81 | This section contains the official HTTP specifications for the target FastAPI endpoints. All endpoints assume a baseline prefix of `/api`. All JSON schemas represent strict Pydantic structures.\n 82 | \n 83 | ---\n 84 | \n 85 | ### 4.1. POST /api/blueprint/generate\n 86 | \n 87 | **Purpose**: Persistently stores and generates an advanced strategic enterprise AI architecture blueprint based on target constraints, compliance frameworks, and infrastructure choices.\n 88 | \n 89 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n 90 | *   **Path**: `/api/blueprint/generate`\n 91 | *   **Security Requirement**: Optional Session Authentication (registers draft anonymously or links to authenticated user profile).\n 92 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n 93 |     ```json\n 94 |     {\n 95 |       \"company_name\": \"Acme Global Enterprise\",\n 96 |       \"industry\": \"Financial Services\",\n 97 |       \"compliance_frameworks\": [\"SOC2\", \"HIPAA\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"],\n 98 |       \"data_residency\": \"EU_WEST\",\n 99 |       \"infrastructure_preference\": \"Sovereign_Cloud\",\n100 |       \"deployment_scale\": \"Enterprise_Wide\",\n101 |       \"selected_capabilities\": [\n102 |         \"Knowledge_Graph_Mesh\",\n103 |         \"Autonomous_Agent_Orchestrators\",\n104 |         \"Governance_Guardrails\"\n105 |       ],\n106 |       \"budget_tier\": \"Premium_Enterprise\"\n107 |     }\n108 |     ```\n109 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n110 |     ```json\n111 |     {\n112 |       \"blueprint_id\": \"blu_908f7e21-3a0c-4991-88b1-38f7e1b99c72\",\n113 |       \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:30:15Z\",\n114 |       \"compliance_rating\": 98.4,\n115 |       \"estimated_deployment_time_weeks\": 12,\n116 |       \"recommended_architecture_nodes\": [\n117 |         {\n118 |           \"id\": \"node-1\",\n119 |           \"label\": \"GFF AI Sovereign Edge\",\n120 |           \"type\": \"infrastructure\",\n121 |           \"status\": \"critical\"\n122 |         },\n123 |         {\n124 |           \"id\": \"node-2\",\n125 |           \"label\": \"Agent Orchestration Mesh\",\n126 |           \"type\": \"orchestrator\",\n127 |           \"status\": \"active\"\n128 |         }\n129 |       ],\n130 |       \"generated_narrative\": \"Based on financial service constraints, GFF AI prescribes a secure, sovereign-hosted multi-agent cluster backed by real-time governance guardrails.\",\n131 |       \"pdf_download_url\": \"https://assets.gff.ai/blueprints/blu_908f7e21_export.pdf\"\n132 |     }\n133 |     ```\n134 | *   **Error Responses**:\n135 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: If empty inputs or incompatibilities exist in selected frameworks.\n136 |     *   `422 Unprocessable Entity`: Validation failure on Pydantic models (e.g. invalid string enum in `data_residency`).\n137 | \n138 | ---\n139 | \n140 | ### 4.2. POST /api/assessment/score\n141 | \n142 | **Purpose**: Takes complex multi-dimensional AI readiness assessments from the client, calculates overall and categorical readiness scores, and maps out targeted remediation paths.\n143 | \n144 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n145 | *   **Path**: `/api/assessment/score`\n146 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Anonymous Access with optional JWT Session linking.\n147 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n148 |     ```json\n149 |     {\n150 |       \"assessment_session_id\": \"sess_89a71b3e\",\n151 |       \"answers\": [\n152 |         { \"question_id\": \"data_strategy_01\", \"score\": 4 },\n153 |         { \"question_id\": \"governance_compliance_02\", \"score\": 2 },\n154 |         { \"question_id\": \"infrastructure_cloud_03\", \"score\": 3 },\n155 |         { \"question_id\": \"talent_readiness_04\", \"score\": 5 },\n156 |         { \"question_id\": \"executive_alignment_05\", \"score\": 2 }\n157 |       ],\n158 |       \"organization_size\": \"10000+\",\n159 |       \"comments\": \"Currently migrating core infrastructure to secure air-gapped systems.\"\n160 |     }\n161 |     ```\n162 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n163 |     ```json\n164 |     {\n165 |       \"assessment_id\": \"asm_10a29b8c-5521-4f93-90be-8a7199c811fa\",\n166 |       \"calculated_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:32:00Z\",\n167 |       \"overall_readiness_score\": 64.0,\n168 |       \"readiness_tier\": \"Strategic Scale-Up\",\n169 |       \"category_scores\": {\n170 |         \"Data & Strategy\": 80.0,\n171 |         \"Governance & Compliance\": 40.0,\n172 |         \"Infrastructure & Cloud\": 60.0,\n173 |         \"Talent & Enablement\": 100.0,\n174 |         \"Executive Alignment\": 40.0\n175 |       },\n176 |       \"remediation_milestones\": [\n177 |         {\n178 |           \"phase\": \"Phase 1: Compliance Foundation\",\n179 |           \"action\": \"Deploy centralized LLM governance guardrails to address the critical 40% Compliance score.\",\n180 |           \"priority\": \"CRITICAL\"\n181 |         },\n182 |         {\n183 |           \"phase\": \"Phase 2: Strategic Executive Roadmap\",\n184 |           \"action\": \"Establish cross-functional steering committee to align on AI ROI parameters.\",\n185 |           \"priority\": \"HIGH\"\n186 |         }\n187 |       ]\n188 |     }\n189 |     ```\n190 | *   **Error Responses**:\n191 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Incomplete questionnaire answers (fewer than the required threshold).\n192 | \n193 | ---\n194 | \n195 | ### 4.3. POST /api/roi/calculate\n196 | \n197 | **Purpose**: Processes custom financial variables, staffing costs, and proposed automation volumes to return complete strategic ROI projections, TCO analyses, and amortization timelines.\n198 | \n199 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n200 | *   **Path**: `/api/roi/calculate`\n201 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Rate-Limited.\n202 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n203 |     ```json\n204 |     {\n205 |       \"annual_revenue\": 500000000,\n206 |       \"employee_count\": 2500,\n207 |       \"average_fte_cost\": 120000,\n208 |       \"current_it_maintenance_spend\": 15000000,\n209 |       \"estimated_agent_deployments\": 50,\n210 |       \"primary_impact_areas\": [\"Customer_Support\", \"Compliance_Audit\", \"Engineering_Velocity\"],\n211 |       \"implementation_horizon_years\": 5\n212 |     }\n213 |     ```\n214 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n215 |     ```json\n216 |     {\n217 |       \"calculation_id\": \"roi_21d7b8ca-889a-4122-b0cc-99ca82b1c7da\",\n218 |       \"financials\": {\n219 |         \"net_present_value\": 4820000.00,\n220 |         \"internal_rate_of_return\": 42.5,\n221 |         \"payback_period_months\": 14,\n222 |         \"five_year_total_savings\": 12450000.00,\n223 |         \"five_year_total_cost_of_ownership\": 2650000.00\n224 |       },\n225 |       \"projected_yearly_breakdown\": [\n226 |         { \"year\": 1, \"costs\": 950000, \"savings\": 1200000, \"net\": 250000 },\n227 |         { \"year\": 2, \"costs\": 450000, \"savings\": 2500000, \"net\": 2050000 },\n228 |         { \"year\": 3, \"costs\": 450000, \"savings\": 2900000, \"net\": 2450000 },\n229 |         { \"year\": 4, \"costs\": 400000, \"savings\": 2900000, \"net\": 2500000 },\n230 |         { \"year\": 5, \"costs\": 400000, \"savings\": 2950000, \"net\": 2550000 }\n231 |       ],\n232 |       \"fte_hours_reallocated_annually\": 85000\n233 |     }\n234 |     ```\n235 | *   **Error Responses**:\n236 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: If impossible numbers are submitted (e.g. employee count is 0 or average cost is negative).\n237 | \n238 | ---\n239 | \n240 | ### 4.4. POST /api/contact/submit\n241 | \n242 | **Purpose**: Processes incoming enterprise-tier lead submissions from the unified Contact module. Automatically sends custom alert notifications via email.\n243 | \n244 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n245 | *   **Path**: `/api/contact/submit`\n246 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Strict Rate-Limiting.\n247 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n248 |     ```json\n249 |     {\n250 |       \"fullName\": \"Elizabeth Vance\",\n251 |       \"fullNameDetail\": \"Elizabeth Vance, VP of Strategy\",\n252 |       \"company\": \"Vance & Co Logistics\",\n253 |       \"companyDetail\": \"Vance & Co Logistics (International Carrier)\",\n254 |       \"businessEmail\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n255 |       \"businessEmailDetail\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com (Primary Office)\",\n256 |       \"estimated_timeline\": \"Immediate (Within 3 months)\",\n257 |       \"message\": \"Interested in deploying Oremesh and Foundry clusters across our operations.\"\n258 |     }\n259 |     ```\n260 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n261 |     ```json\n262 |     {\n263 |       \"success\": true,\n264 |       \"submission_id\": \"contact_9a87cdb1-21e0-40e8-b80c-e87f21a8b9e1\",\n265 |       \"submitted_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:35:12Z\",\n266 |       \"message\": \"Thank you. An Enterprise Integration Executive will reach out within 4 business hours.\"\n267 |     }\n268 |     ```\n269 | *   **Error Responses**:\n270 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Validation failure (e.g. missing fields, invalid email address format).\n271 |     *   `429 Too Many Requests`: Rate limit exceeded on contact submission IP or email address.\n272 | \n273 | ---\n274 | \n275 | ### 4.5. POST /api/proposal/generate\n276 | \n277 | **Purpose**: Compiles client-defined custom requirements, timelines, budget allocations, and architectural structures to construct a complete RFP / GFF AI Engagement Proposal.\n278 | \n279 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n280 | *   **Path**: `/api/proposal/generate`\n281 | *   **Security Requirement**: Authenticated Session / Valid OTP Session Token.\n282 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n283 |     ```json\n284 |     {\n285 |       \"rfp_id\": \"rfp_782ab912\",\n286 |       \"compliance_stipulations\": [\"SOC2_TYPE_II\", \"ISO_27001\"],\n287 |       \"strategic_objectives\": [\n288 |         \"Reduce operational cost by 30%\",\n289 |         \"Automate multi-agent document review with human-in-the-loop\"\n290 |       ],\n291 |       \"proposed_timeline_weeks\": 16,\n292 |       \"key_milestones_requested\": [\n293 |         \"Architecture Co-Design\",\n294 |         \"Foundry Studio Workflow Verification\",\n295 |         \"Full Edge Production Launch\"\n296 |       ],\n297 |       \"budget_cap\": 750000\n298 |     }\n299 |     ```\n300 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n301 |     ```json\n302 |     {\n303 |       \"proposal_id\": \"prp_bc82a17f-1c09-4d9d-9a99-b8efc892a01f\",\n304 |       \"generated_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:38:40Z\",\n305 |       \"download_url\": \"https://assets.gff.ai/proposals/prp_bc82a17f_export.pdf\",\n306 |       \"financial_schedule\": {\n307 |         \"foundational_licensing\": 180000.00,\n308 |         \"custom_edge_engineering\": 240000.00,\n309 |         \"operational_governance_setup\": 100000.00,\n310 |         \"contingency_reserve\": 50000.00,\n311 |         \"total_estimated_value\": 570000.00\n312 |       },\n313 |       \"suggested_delivery_stages\": [\n314 |         { \"milestone\": \"Co-Design Workshop\", \"weeks_from_kickoff\": 2, \"description\": \"Full alignment of network topology and data flows\" },\n315 |         { \"milestone\": \"Foundry Studio DAG Validation\", \"weeks_from_kickoff\": 8, \"description\": \"Compilation of all active agent models inside standard mock runs\" },\n316 |         { \"milestone\": \"Sovereign Production Buildout\", \"weeks_from_kickoff\": 16, \"description\": \"Final governance keys transferred to target enterprise team\" }\n317 |       ]\n318 |     }\n319 |     ```\n320 | *   **Error Responses**:\n321 |     *   `401 Unauthorized`: Session token is absent, expired, or invalid.\n322 |     *   `422 Unprocessable Entity`: Input is out of acceptable project scopes or budget boundaries.\n323 | \n324 | ---\n325 | \n326 | ### 4.6. POST /api/auth/request-otp\n327 | \n328 | **Purpose**: Dispatches a highly secure 6-digit One-Time Password to verified enterprise business emails. Blocks public disposable email domains.\n329 | \n330 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n331 | *   **Path**: `/api/auth/request-otp`\n332 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / High-Sensitivity Rate-Limiter (prevents spam and brute-force).\n333 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n334 |     ```json\n335 |     {\n336 |       \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\"\n337 |     }\n338 |     ```\n339 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n340 |     ```json\n341 |     {\n342 |       \"status\": \"sent\",\n343 |       \"temporary_tracking_id\": \"otp_82a1bc23\",\n344 |       \"expires_in_seconds\": 600,\n345 |       \"message\": \"A 6-digit access code has been dispatched. Please verify within 10 minutes.\"\n346 |     }\n347 |     ```\n348 | *   **Error Responses**:\n349 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Non-corporate domain rejected (e.g. gmail.com, mailinator.com are blocked).\n350 |     *   `429 Too Many Requests`: Strict verification cooldown period (must wait 60 seconds before requesting another code).\n351 | \n352 | ---\n353 | \n354 | ### 4.7. POST /api/auth/verify-otp\n355 | \n356 | **Purpose**: Verifies the dispatched One-Time Password against cached Redis entries. If valid, generates a secure, HTTP-only cookie and JWT Access Token to authenticate all subsequently protected platform requests.\n357 | \n358 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n359 | *   **Path**: `/api/auth/verify-otp`\n360 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Anti-Brute-Force Lock-out.\n361 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n362 |     ```json\n363 |     {\n364 |       \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n365 |       \"otp_code\": \"481029\",\n366 |       \"device_identifier\": \"Chrome_Mac_10.15.7\"\n367 |     }\n368 |     ```\n369 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n370 |     ```json\n371 |     {\n372 |       \"access_token\": \"gff_jwt_ey298ac1002b8d9c028e1837a28...37281\",\n373 |       \"token_type\": \"bearer\",\n374 |       \"expires_in_seconds\": 86400,\n375 |       \"user_profile\": {\n376 |         \"id\": \"usr_9a82cdbf-12a0-4050-9fbe-3891cfae82ab\",\n377 |         \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n378 |         \"organization\": \"Vance & Co Logistics\",\n379 |         \"assigned_role\": \"Enterprise_Strategy_Lead\",\n380 |         \"verified_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:41:02Z\"\n381 |       }\n382 |     }\n383 |     ```\n384 | *   **Error Responses**:\n385 |     *   `401 Unauthorized`: Code mismatch, invalid code, or code has expired.\n386 |     *   `429 Too Many Requests`: Maximum of 3 consecutive invalid code attempts allowed before account email is locked out for 15 minutes.\n387 | \n388 | ---\n389 | \n390 | ### 4.8. POST /api/newsletter/subscribe\n391 | \n392 | **Purpose**: Seamlessly registers a user to receive high-fidelity research alerts, whitepapers, and corporate patterns of intelligence updates.\n393 | \n394 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n395 | *   **Path**: `/api/newsletter/subscribe`\n396 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Rate-Limited.\n397 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n398 |     ```json\n399 |     {\n400 |       \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n401 |       \"consent_acknowledged\": true,\n402 |       \"preferred_topics\": [\"Architectures\", \"Sovereign_AI\", \"Case_Studies\"]\n403 |     }\n404 |     ```\n405 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n406 |     ```json\n407 |     {\n408 |       \"status\": \"subscription_initiated\",\n409 |       \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n410 |       \"confirmation_required\": true,\n411 |       \"message\": \"Opt-in confirmation sent. Please verify your subscription from your inbox.\"\n412 |     }\n413 |     ```\n414 | *   **Error Responses**:\n415 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Email already subscribed, or consent checkbox is false.\n416 | \n417 | ---\n418 | \n419 | ### 4.9. POST /api/sandbox/run\n420 | \n421 | **Purpose**: Compiles custom client-configured system instructions, agent definitions, and sandbox scenarios. Returns complete visual trace logs, step metrics, and simulated model tokens.\n422 | \n423 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n424 | *   **Path**: `/api/sandbox/run`\n425 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Session-Bound.\n426 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n427 |     ```json\n428 |     {\n429 |       \"system_prompt\": \"You are a secure compliance supervisor agent analyzing transaction streams.\",\n430 |       \"agent_temperature\": 0.2,\n431 |       \"tools_enabled\": [\"database_query\", \"compliance_checker\"],\n432 |       \"query_input\": \"Validate transaction #TRX-98210 for typical AML issues.\",\n433 |       \"simulation_depth\": \"comprehensive\"\n434 |     }\n435 |     ```\n436 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n437 |     ```json\n438 |     {\n439 |       \"execution_id\": \"exe_892ba09c-33b0-4f90-a3bc-99ba8201fa90\",\n440 |       \"status\": \"completed\",\n441 |       \"execution_time_ms\": 1420,\n442 |       \"token_metrics\": {\n443 |         \"input_tokens\": 420,\n444 |         \"output_tokens\": 280,\n445 |         \"simulated_cost_usd\": 0.0042\n446 |       },\n447 |       \"execution_trace_logs\": [\n448 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:00.100\", \"actor\": \"Supervisor Agent\", \"action\": \"Initialize Task Parsing\", \"detail\": \"Analyzing user query for transaction reference TRX-98210.\" },\n449 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:00.520\", \"actor\": \"database_query\", \"action\": \"Querying secure transaction DB\", \"detail\": \"Returned payload: {amount: $450,000, origin: Sovereign_Acc_92}\" },\n450 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:01.110\", \"actor\": \"compliance_checker\", \"action\": \"Rules evaluation\", \"detail\": \"Evaluating rules under EU AI Act & AML regulations. Compliance tier verified.\" }\n451 |       ],\n452 |       \"final_output_text\": \"Compliance trace verified successfully. No active threat indicators detected for TRX-98210. Isolation protocols are negative.\"\n453 |     }\n454 |     ```\n455 | *   **Error Responses**:\n456 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Malformed execution parameters or unsupported sandbox tools.\n457 |     *   `500 Internal Server Error`: Execution sandbox simulation failed or timed out.\n458 | \n459 | ---\n460 | \n461 | ### 4.10. POST /api/foundry/workflow\n462 | \n463 | **Purpose**: Compiles a directed acyclic graph (DAG) workflow topology designed in the Foundry Studio canvas. Automatically checks for dead ends, loose ports, or circular dependency errors.\n464 | \n465 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n466 | *   **Path**: `/api/foundry/workflow`\n467 | *   **Security Requirement**: Authenticated Session / OTP Verified.\n468 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n469 |     ```json\n470 |     {\n471 |       \"canvas_id\": \"canvas_foundry_821\",\n472 |       \"workflow_name\": \"Procurement Audit Pipeline\",\n473 |       \"nodes\": [\n474 |         { \"id\": \"n-1\", \"type\": \"ingestion\", \"label\": \"Document Scanner\", \"config\": { \"source\": \"RFP_Folder\" } },\n475 |         { \"id\": \"n-2\", \"type\": \"agent\", \"label\": \"Risk Analyzer\", \"config\": { \"model\": \"gff-sovereign-large\", \"temp\": 0.0 } },\n476 |         { \"id\": \"n-3\", \"type\": \"action\", \"label\": \"Compliance Sign-off\", \"config\": { \"approver_role\": \"Compliance_VP\" } }\n477 |       ],\n478 |       \"edges\": [\n479 |         { \"id\": \"e-1-2\", \"source\": \"n-1\", \"target\": \"n-2\" },\n480 |         { \"id\": \"e-2-3\", \"source\": \"n-2\", \"target\": \"n-3\" }\n481 |       ]\n482 |     }\n483 |     ```\n484 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n485 |     ```json\n486 |     {\n487 |       \"workflow_id\": \"wfl_ff8a02bd-2210-4c7b-a1bc-7cde92a017fa\",\n488 |       \"status\": \"validated_and_saved\",\n489 |       \"last_updated\": \"2026-06-27T10:48:15Z\",\n490 |       \"validation_report\": {\n491 |         \"is_valid_dag\": true,\n492 |         \"cycles_detected\": false,\n493 |         \"dangling_nodes_count\": 0,\n494 |         \"issues_logged\": []\n495 |       },\n496 |       \"deployment_manifest_hash\": \"sha256_e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855\"\n497 |     }\n498 |     ```\n499 | *   **Error Responses**:\n500 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Invalid canvas layout structure.\n501 |     *   `401 Unauthorized`: Session token is invalid or missing.\n502 | \n503 | ---\n504 | \n505 | ### 4.11. GET /api/marketplace/agents\n506 | \n507 | **Purpose**: Queries and paginates pre-configured, enterprise-ready specialized GFF AI agents for integration.\n508 | \n509 | *   **HTTP Method**: `GET`\n510 | *   **Path**: `/api/marketplace/agents`\n511 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public (Read-Only Portal).\n512 | *   **Query Parameters**:\n513 |     *   `category` (string, optional): e.g. \"finance\", \"compliance\"\n514 |     *   `industry` (string, optional): e.g. \"energy\", \"telecom\"\n515 |     *   `certification` (string, optional): e.g. \"SOC2\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"\n516 |     *   `search_term` (string, optional): e.g. \"sovereign\"\n517 |     *   `page` (int, default: 1)\n518 |     *   `page_size` (int, default: 12)\n519 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n520 |     ```json\n521 |     {\n522 |       \"agents\": [\n523 |         {\n524 |           \"agent_id\": \"agt_01_sovereign_tax\",\n525 |           \"name\": \"Sovereign Audit & Tax Inspector\",\n526 |           \"description\": \"High-assurance specialist agent configured specifically to audit cross-border tax pipelines under sovereign legal frameworks.\",\n527 |           \"author\": \"GFF AI Core Labs\",\n528 |           \"category\": \"Tax & Finance\",\n529 |           \"certifications\": [\"SOC2\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"],\n530 |           \"cost_per_million_tokens\": 12.50,\n531 |           \"popularity_score\": 4.9,\n532 |           \"icon_slug\": \"shield-tax\"\n533 |         }\n534 |       ],\n535 |       \"pagination\": {\n536 |         \"total_items\": 1,\n537 |         \"total_pages\": 1,\n538 |         \"current_page\": 1,\n539 |         \"page_size\": 12\n540 |       }\n541 |     }\n542 |     ```\n543 | *   **Error Responses**:\n544 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Invalid pagination numbers or unrecognized filter parameters.\n545 | \n546 | ---\n547 | \n548 | ## 5. Security & Environment Configuration Templates\n549 | \n550 | To ensure proper operational continuity when moving from client-side simulation to server execution, the backend requires a strict configuration schema. Below is the production-grade, fully documented `.env.example` template that defines the service bindings.\n551 | \n552 | ### 5.1. Target `.env.example` File\n553 | \n554 | ```bash\n555 | # ==============================================================================\n556 | # GFF AI PLATFORM: ENTERPRISE FASTAPI ENGINE - ENVIRONMENT BINDINGS\n557 | # ==============================================================================\n558 | \n559 | # --- PLATFORM CORE ---\n560 | APP_NAME=\"GFF AI Enterprise Platform Backend\"\n561 | APP_ENV=\"production\" # options: development, staging, production\n562 | DEBUG=false\n563 | SECRET_KEY=\"replace-with-a-64-character-cryptographically-secure-hex-string\"\n564 | ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440 # 24 hours\n565 | \n566 | # --- NETWORKING & CORS CORRIDORS ---\n567 | # Comma-separated list of fully-qualified client-facing origin domains\n568 | ALLOWED_HOSTS=\"https://gff.ai,https://www.gff.ai,https://build.gff.ai\"\n569 | PORT=8000\n570 | HOST=\"0.0.0.0\"\n571 | \n572 | # --- RELATIONAL STORAGE (POSTGRESQL) ---\n573 | DATABASE_HOST=\"postgres.internal.gff.ai\"\n574 | DATABASE_PORT=5432\n575 | DATABASE_USER=\"gff_sec_admin\"\n576 | DATABASE_PASSWORD=\"secure_database_password_placeholder\"\n577 | DATABASE_NAME=\"gff_ai_core\"\n578 | DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=20\n579 | DATABASE_MAX_OVERFLOW=10\n580 | \n581 | # --- IN-MEMORY SESSION & CACHE STORE (REDIS) ---\n582 | REDIS_HOST=\"redis.internal.gff.ai\"\n583 | REDIS_PORT=6379\n584 | REDIS_DB=0\n585 | REDIS_PASSWORD=\"secure_redis_password_placeholder\"\n586 | REDIS_SSL=true\n587 | \n588 | # --- SECURE EMAIL & OTP DISPATCHER ---\n589 | # Integration credentials for sending corporate verification keys\n590 | SMTP_HOST=\"smtp.mailgun.org\"\n591 | SMTP_PORT=587\n592 | SMTP_USER=\"postmaster@mg.gff.ai\"\n593 | SMTP_PASSWORD=\"secure_smtp_password_placeholder\"\n594 | CONTACT_RECEIVER_EMAIL=\"ceohirezapp@gmail.com\"\n595 | \n596 | # --- SECURE S3 OBJECT REPOSITORY ---\n597 | # For archiving dynamic proposals, architectures, and compiled logs.\n598 | # DO NOT hardcode real credentials in development or repository environments.\n599 | AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=\"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID_REPLACE\"\n600 | AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=\"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY_REPLACE\"\n601 | AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=\"eu-west-1\"\n602 | AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=\"gff-enterprise-assets\"\n603 | AWS_S3_ENDPOINT_URL=\"https://s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com\" # custom endpoint for sovereign-compatible clouds\n604 | \n605 | # --- AGENT SANDBOX INTERPRETER (EPHEMERAL RUNTIMES) ---\n606 | SANDBOX_TIMEOUT_MS=5000\n607 | SANDBOX_MAX_MEMORY_MB=128\n608 | SANDBOX_EXECUTION_MODE=\"isolated_sandbox_container\"\n609 | ```\n610 | \n611 | ---\n612 | \n613 | ## 6. Local State Synchronization Strategy (Phase 4 Migration Guide)\n614 | \n615 | When executing the integration, use the following operational mapping to safely transition without breaking existing user flows:\n616 | \n617 | 1. **State Hydration**: On page mount within Next.js, read from client-side `localStorage` or session store. If user authenticates via OTP (`POST /api/auth/verify-otp`), retrieve the corresponding persistent record from the server and hydrate the local React state.\n618 | 2. **Optimistic UI Updates**: Keep calculating calculations client-side dynamically (for fluid animations and responsive interactions), but dispatch a background debounce request to `/api/blueprint/generate` or `/api/roi/calculate` to sync and freeze the official calculated blueprint or ROI sheet.\n619 | 3. **Graceful Fallbacks**: If the FastAPI backend is temporarily unreachable, the frontend tools will catch the error, log it securely, and revert seamlessly to local Web-Worker simulation mode. This ensures high availability and 100% uptime of the strategic interactive tool visualizer.\n620 | ","success":true}],"durationMs":8}}
