{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:37:48.371Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"2g8h9y8l","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md:401-620","result":"401 |       \"consent_acknowledged\": true,\n402 |       \"preferred_topics\": [\"Architectures\", \"Sovereign_AI\", \"Case_Studies\"]\n403 |     }\n404 |     ```\n405 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n406 |     ```json\n407 |     {\n408 |       \"status\": \"subscription_initiated\",\n409 |       \"email\": \"evance@vancelogistics.com\",\n410 |       \"confirmation_required\": true,\n411 |       \"message\": \"Opt-in confirmation sent. Please verify your subscription from your inbox.\"\n412 |     }\n413 |     ```\n414 | *   **Error Responses**:\n415 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Email already subscribed, or consent checkbox is false.\n416 | \n417 | ---\n418 | \n419 | ### 4.9. POST /api/sandbox/run\n420 | \n421 | **Purpose**: Compiles custom client-configured system instructions, agent definitions, and sandbox scenarios. Returns complete visual trace logs, step metrics, and simulated model tokens.\n422 | \n423 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n424 | *   **Path**: `/api/sandbox/run`\n425 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Session-Bound.\n426 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n427 |     ```json\n428 |     {\n429 |       \"system_prompt\": \"You are a secure compliance supervisor agent analyzing transaction streams.\",\n430 |       \"agent_temperature\": 0.2,\n431 |       \"tools_enabled\": [\"database_query\", \"compliance_checker\"],\n432 |       \"query_input\": \"Validate transaction #TRX-98210 for typical AML issues.\",\n433 |       \"simulation_depth\": \"comprehensive\"\n434 |     }\n435 |     ```\n436 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n437 |     ```json\n438 |     {\n439 |       \"execution_id\": \"exe_892ba09c-33b0-4f90-a3bc-99ba8201fa90\",\n440 |       \"status\": \"completed\",\n441 |       \"execution_time_ms\": 1420,\n442 |       \"token_metrics\": {\n443 |         \"input_tokens\": 420,\n444 |         \"output_tokens\": 280,\n445 |         \"simulated_cost_usd\": 0.0042\n446 |       },\n447 |       \"execution_trace_logs\": [\n448 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:00.100\", \"actor\": \"Supervisor Agent\", \"action\": \"Initialize Task Parsing\", \"detail\": \"Analyzing user query for transaction reference TRX-98210.\" },\n449 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:00.520\", \"actor\": \"database_query\", \"action\": \"Querying secure transaction DB\", \"detail\": \"Returned payload: {amount: $450,000, origin: Sovereign_Acc_92}\" },\n450 |         { \"timestamp\": \"10:45:01.110\", \"actor\": \"compliance_checker\", \"action\": \"Rules evaluation\", \"detail\": \"Evaluating rules under EU AI Act & AML regulations. Compliance tier verified.\" }\n451 |       ],\n452 |       \"final_output_text\": \"Compliance trace verified successfully. No active threat indicators detected for TRX-98210. Isolation protocols are negative.\"\n453 |     }\n454 |     ```\n455 | *   **Error Responses**:\n456 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Malformed execution parameters or unsupported sandbox tools.\n457 |     *   `500 Internal Server Error`: Execution sandbox simulation failed or timed out.\n458 | \n459 | ---\n460 | \n461 | ### 4.10. POST /api/foundry/workflow\n462 | \n463 | **Purpose**: Compiles a directed acyclic graph (DAG) workflow topology designed in the Foundry Studio canvas. Automatically checks for dead ends, loose ports, or circular dependency errors.\n464 | \n465 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n466 | *   **Path**: `/api/foundry/workflow`\n467 | *   **Security Requirement**: Authenticated Session / OTP Verified.\n468 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n469 |     ```json\n470 |     {\n471 |       \"canvas_id\": \"canvas_foundry_821\",\n472 |       \"workflow_name\": \"Procurement Audit Pipeline\",\n473 |       \"nodes\": [\n474 |         { \"id\": \"n-1\", \"type\": \"ingestion\", \"label\": \"Document Scanner\", \"config\": { \"source\": \"RFP_Folder\" } },\n475 |         { \"id\": \"n-2\", \"type\": \"agent\", \"label\": \"Risk Analyzer\", \"config\": { \"model\": \"gff-sovereign-large\", \"temp\": 0.0 } },\n476 |         { \"id\": \"n-3\", \"type\": \"action\", \"label\": \"Compliance Sign-off\", \"config\": { \"approver_role\": \"Compliance_VP\" } }\n477 |       ],\n478 |       \"edges\": [\n479 |         { \"id\": \"e-1-2\", \"source\": \"n-1\", \"target\": \"n-2\" },\n480 |         { \"id\": \"e-2-3\", \"source\": \"n-2\", \"target\": \"n-3\" }\n481 |       ]\n482 |     }\n483 |     ```\n484 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n485 |     ```json\n486 |     {\n487 |       \"workflow_id\": \"wfl_ff8a02bd-2210-4c7b-a1bc-7cde92a017fa\",\n488 |       \"status\": \"validated_and_saved\",\n489 |       \"last_updated\": \"2026-06-27T10:48:15Z\",\n490 |       \"validation_report\": {\n491 |         \"is_valid_dag\": true,\n492 |         \"cycles_detected\": false,\n493 |         \"dangling_nodes_count\": 0,\n494 |         \"issues_logged\": []\n495 |       },\n496 |       \"deployment_manifest_hash\": \"sha256_e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855\"\n497 |     }\n498 |     ```\n499 | *   **Error Responses**:\n500 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Invalid canvas layout structure.\n501 |     *   `401 Unauthorized`: Session token is invalid or missing.\n502 | \n503 | ---\n504 | \n505 | ### 4.11. GET /api/marketplace/agents\n506 | \n507 | **Purpose**: Queries and paginates pre-configured, enterprise-ready specialized GFF AI agents for integration.\n508 | \n509 | *   **HTTP Method**: `GET`\n510 | *   **Path**: `/api/marketplace/agents`\n511 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public (Read-Only Portal).\n512 | *   **Query Parameters**:\n513 |     *   `category` (string, optional): e.g. \"finance\", \"compliance\"\n514 |     *   `industry` (string, optional): e.g. \"energy\", \"telecom\"\n515 |     *   `certification` (string, optional): e.g. \"SOC2\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"\n516 |     *   `search_term` (string, optional): e.g. \"sovereign\"\n517 |     *   `page` (int, default: 1)\n518 |     *   `page_size` (int, default: 12)\n519 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n520 |     ```json\n521 |     {\n522 |       \"agents\": [\n523 |         {\n524 |           \"agent_id\": \"agt_01_sovereign_tax\",\n525 |           \"name\": \"Sovereign Audit & Tax Inspector\",\n526 |           \"description\": \"High-assurance specialist agent configured specifically to audit cross-border tax pipelines under sovereign legal frameworks.\",\n527 |           \"author\": \"GFF AI Core Labs\",\n528 |           \"category\": \"Tax & Finance\",\n529 |           \"certifications\": [\"SOC2\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"],\n530 |           \"cost_per_million_tokens\": 12.50,\n531 |           \"popularity_score\": 4.9,\n532 |           \"icon_slug\": \"shield-tax\"\n533 |         }\n534 |       ],\n535 |       \"pagination\": {\n536 |         \"total_items\": 1,\n537 |         \"total_pages\": 1,\n538 |         \"current_page\": 1,\n539 |         \"page_size\": 12\n540 |       }\n541 |     }\n542 |     ```\n543 | *   **Error Responses**:\n544 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: Invalid pagination numbers or unrecognized filter parameters.\n545 | \n546 | ---\n547 | \n548 | ## 5. Security & Environment Configuration Templates\n549 | \n550 | To ensure proper operational continuity when moving from client-side simulation to server execution, the backend requires a strict configuration schema. Below is the production-grade, fully documented `.env.example` template that defines the service bindings.\n551 | \n552 | ### 5.1. Target `.env.example` File\n553 | \n554 | ```bash\n555 | # ==============================================================================\n556 | # GFF AI PLATFORM: ENTERPRISE FASTAPI ENGINE - ENVIRONMENT BINDINGS\n557 | # ==============================================================================\n558 | \n559 | # --- PLATFORM CORE ---\n560 | APP_NAME=\"GFF AI Enterprise Platform Backend\"\n561 | APP_ENV=\"production\" # options: development, staging, production\n562 | DEBUG=false\n563 | SECRET_KEY=\"replace-with-a-64-character-cryptographically-secure-hex-string\"\n564 | ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440 # 24 hours\n565 | \n566 | # --- NETWORKING & CORS CORRIDORS ---\n567 | # Comma-separated list of fully-qualified client-facing origin domains\n568 | ALLOWED_HOSTS=\"https://gff.ai,https://www.gff.ai,https://build.gff.ai\"\n569 | PORT=8000\n570 | HOST=\"0.0.0.0\"\n571 | \n572 | # --- RELATIONAL STORAGE (POSTGRESQL) ---\n573 | DATABASE_HOST=\"postgres.internal.gff.ai\"\n574 | DATABASE_PORT=5432\n575 | DATABASE_USER=\"gff_sec_admin\"\n576 | DATABASE_PASSWORD=\"secure_database_password_placeholder\"\n577 | DATABASE_NAME=\"gff_ai_core\"\n578 | DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=20\n579 | DATABASE_MAX_OVERFLOW=10\n580 | \n581 | # --- IN-MEMORY SESSION & CACHE STORE (REDIS) ---\n582 | REDIS_HOST=\"redis.internal.gff.ai\"\n583 | REDIS_PORT=6379\n584 | REDIS_DB=0\n585 | REDIS_PASSWORD=\"secure_redis_password_placeholder\"\n586 | REDIS_SSL=true\n587 | \n588 | # --- SECURE EMAIL & OTP DISPATCHER ---\n589 | # Integration credentials for sending corporate verification keys\n590 | SMTP_HOST=\"smtp.mailgun.org\"\n591 | SMTP_PORT=587\n592 | SMTP_USER=\"postmaster@mg.gff.ai\"\n593 | SMTP_PASSWORD=\"secure_smtp_password_placeholder\"\n594 | CONTACT_RECEIVER_EMAIL=\"ceohirezapp@gmail.com\"\n595 | \n596 | # --- SECURE S3 OBJECT REPOSITORY ---\n597 | # For archiving dynamic proposals, architectures, and compiled logs.\n598 | # DO NOT hardcode real credentials in development or repository environments.\n599 | AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=\"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID_REPLACE\"\n600 | AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=\"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY_REPLACE\"\n601 | AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=\"eu-west-1\"\n602 | AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=\"gff-enterprise-assets\"\n603 | AWS_S3_ENDPOINT_URL=\"https://s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com\" # custom endpoint for sovereign-compatible clouds\n604 | \n605 | # --- AGENT SANDBOX INTERPRETER (EPHEMERAL RUNTIMES) ---\n606 | SANDBOX_TIMEOUT_MS=5000\n607 | SANDBOX_MAX_MEMORY_MB=128\n608 | SANDBOX_EXECUTION_MODE=\"isolated_sandbox_container\"\n609 | ```\n610 | \n611 | ---\n612 | \n613 | ## 6. Local State Synchronization Strategy (Phase 4 Migration Guide)\n614 | \n615 | When executing the integration, use the following operational mapping to safely transition without breaking existing user flows:\n616 | \n617 | 1. **State Hydration**: On page mount within Next.js, read from client-side `localStorage` or session store. If user authenticates via OTP (`POST /api/auth/verify-otp`), retrieve the corresponding persistent record from the server and hydrate the local React state.\n618 | 2. **Optimistic UI Updates**: Keep calculating calculations client-side dynamically (for fluid animations and responsive interactions), but dispatch a background debounce request to `/api/blueprint/generate` or `/api/roi/calculate` to sync and freeze the official calculated blueprint or ROI sheet.\n619 | 3. **Graceful Fallbacks**: If the FastAPI backend is temporarily unreachable, the frontend tools will catch the error, log it securely, and revert seamlessly to local Web-Worker simulation mode. This ensures high availability and 100% uptime of the strategic interactive tool visualizer.\n620 | ","success":true}],"durationMs":16}}
